<div1 type="letter">

<pb facs="nei.j4c.64.36" />

<fw type="curatorial">36</fw>

<opener>
<dateline>
5835 Vine Street<lb/>
Lincoln, Nebraska 68505<lb/>
November 29, 1972
</dateline>

<address>
<addrLine>Mrs. Anne Deirup</addrLine>
<addrLine>1629 Josephine Street</addrLine>
<addrLine>Berkeley, California 94703</addrLine>
</address>

<salute>Dear Anne Deirup:</salute>
</opener>
<p>It was good to hear from you, and I am certainly pleased that you will give Mab's first editions of my work to the Neihardt Foundation at Bancroft, Nebraska, when the proper time comes.</p>

<p>The Foundation is a new organization and has only recently begun to buy land for a museum they intend to build.</p>

<p>Bancroft is a little town in Nebraska on the border of the Omaha Indian Reservation. It was my home during my youth and for years while I was writing some of my best known books. The Foundation has restored my old study and developed a little park about it near my former home. Also it has built a beautiful Sioux Prayer Garden as a memorial. The "Neihardt Center" is listed as a national historical site, and many tourists visit it every summer.</p>
<closer>
<salute>With affectionate thoughts,</salute>


<signed>John G. Neihardt</signed>

<note>JGN:nh</note> 
</closer>

</div1>
